{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2d1bd58-3d4f-402d-beaa-e488cb56c925","content":"Here's the setup:\n\n**AppShell.xaml**\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<Shell x:Class=\"MyApp.AppShell\"\n       xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n       xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n       xmlns:views=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.Views\"\n       FlyoutBehavior=\"Flyout\">\n\n    <!-- Dashboard (single page) -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Dashboard\" Icon=\"dashboard.png\">\n        <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:DashboardPage}\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Products (two tabs) -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Products\" Icon=\"products.png\">\n        <Tab Title=\"Active\">\n            <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ActiveProductsPage}\" />\n        </Tab>\n        <Tab Title=\"Archived\">\n            <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ArchivedProductsPage}\" />\n        </Tab>\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Settings -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Settings\" Icon=\"settings.png\">\n        <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:SettingsPage}\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n</Shell>\n```\n\n**AppShell.xaml.cs** — register the detail route here:\n```csharp\nnamespace MyApp;\n\npublic partial class AppShell : Shell\n{\n    public AppShell()\n    {\n        InitializeComponent();\n\n        // Register routes for pages not in the visual hierarchy\n        Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(Views.ProductDetailsPage), typeof(Views.ProductDetailsPage));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Navigating to the detail page** (e.g., from a list item tap):\n```csharp\nawait Shell.Current.GoToAsync($\"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?id={product.Id}\");\n```\n\n**Receiving the parameter** in `ProductDetailsPage`:\n```csharp\n[QueryProperty(nameof(ProductId), \"id\")]\npublic partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage\n{\n    public string ProductId { get; set; }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `FlyoutItem` creates top-level flyout entries.\n- Nesting multiple `<Tab>` elements inside a `FlyoutItem` gives you the bottom tab bar within that section.\n- `Routing.RegisterRoute` is used for pages that aren't part of the shell's visual tree (like detail/push pages).\n- `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` defers page creation until navigation (better perf).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe04ff10-0be7-4d24-9117-27b88af81291","outputTokens":650,"requestId":"A847:211CBF:6F0B9A:802A16:69FBE4EA"},"id":"6127cdbe-845f-42dd-a843-9a26065c18da","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:03:49.467Z","parentId":"e784b62d-af22-437e-961d-6f0c2967d5d6"}
